docs.lead_paragraph: DOCTOR ZAIUS, a pop-punk trio from Anchorage, is going to play the most important concert of its 18-month career tomorrow night, at Don Hill's in Greenwich Village. "At this point, this concert is our only shot," said Zall Shedlock, the band's 23-year-old bassist. "I think, after paying to get to New York, each of us is going to be broke for a while. We'll probably end up spending $3,000 altogether, and that doesn't count the tapes and stickers we had to make."
